# EMA Project — In-Depth Walkthrough

## What Is This Project?

**EMA (Expense Management Audit)** is a full-stack web application for monitoring and auditing expense-related SQL Server Agent jobs and data quality. It connects to a central **MSSQL database** (`EMA_Support_Module`) and dynamically discovers client databases to analyze expense records, receipts, reconciliation, and data flags.

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Frontend ["Frontend (React 19 + Vite)"]
        App["App.jsx — Router"]
        Pages["7 Page Modules"]
        API["API Layer (Axios + React Query)"]
    end

    subgraph Backend ["Backend (Express 5 + Node.js)"]
        Server["server.js — Entry Point"]
        MW["JWT Auth Middleware"]
        Routes["10 Route Modules"]
    end

    subgraph DB ["Database (MSSQL)"]
        EMA["EMA_Support_Module"]
        ClientDBs["Dynamic Client DBs"]
    end

    App --> Pages
    Pages --> API
    API -->|HTTP + JWT| Server
    Server --> MW --> Routes
    Routes -->|mssql driver| EMA
    EMA -.->|Dynamic SQL| ClientDBs
```

